• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Portfolio Committee on Higher Education and Training  is to receive an update on the R14-million that was erroneously paid to a Walter Sisulu University (WSU) student in June. WSU, the National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) and Intellimali, which disburses funds on NSFAS's behalf, will attend. Intellimali has laid a charge of theft against the student who received the money, Sibongile Mani, after she spent more than R800,000 of it WATCH: Students mob recipient of R14 million The committee will also meet with the University of Zululand and the Mangosuthu University of Technology on governance challenges. eNCA